            <title><![CDATA[Nintendo Reveals The Final Trailer For The Super Mario Galaxy Movie And Voice Cast For Yoshi, Wart, and More]]></title>
            <link>https://gameinformer.com/2026/03/09/nintendo-reveals-the-final-trailer-for-the-super-mario-galaxy-movie-and-voice-cast-for</link>
            <guid>1458061</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div property="schema:text"><p>As <a href="https://gameinformer.com/2026/03/06/the-final-trailer-for-the-super-mario-galaxy-movie-airs-on-monday">announced last Friday</a>, Nintendo has released the final trailer for <em>The Super Mario Bros. Movie</em> today ahead of its premiere next month (and, strangely, before Mar10 Day tomorrow). Nintendo also revealed some surprising casting choices for the remaining big characters.</p><p>The last trailer gives us a look at Yoshi in action as Mario’s faithful steed, Bowser Jr. joining up with his angry papa, and a surprising amount of Super Mario Bros. 2 representation. Check it out below.&nbsp;</p><p height="360" width="640" url="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LX9kXRRJlPw"><iframe width="640" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LX9kXRRJlPw" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay" allowfullscreen="true">&nbsp;</iframe></p><p>The Direct also revealed the following actors will voice Yoshi, Wart, and Honey Queen:</p>



<article data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="938ca923-eeb6-4fd2-942b-e990773cf0d6" data-embed-button="image_browser_uploader" data-entity-embed-display="image:responsive_image" data-entity-embed-display-settings="{&quot;responsive_image_style&quot;:&quot;content_body&quot;,&quot;image_loading&quot;:{&quot;attribute&quot;:&quot;lazy&quot;},&quot;image_link&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;link_url&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;link_target&quot;:0,&quot;link_original&quot;:0,&quot;image_source&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;embed_source&quot;:0,&quot;image_caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;embed_caption&quot;:0,&quot;content_warning&quot;:0}" data-langcode="en">

  
          <picture>
                  <source srcset="https://gameinformer.com/sites/default/files/styles/body_default/public/2026/03/09/5db549a0/supermariogalaxymovie_donaldglover.jpg.webp 1x" media="all and (min-width: 851px)" type="image/webp" width="800" height="450">
              <source srcset="https://gameinformer.com/sites/default/files/styles/content_default_mobile_/public/2026/03/09/5db549a0/supermariogalaxymovie_donaldglover.jpg.webp 1x" media="all and (min-width: 315px) and (max-width: 450px)" type="image/webp" width="450" height="253">
              <source srcset="https://gameinformer.com/sites/default/files/styles/content_default_mobile_/public/2026/03/09/5db549a0/supermariogalaxymovie_donaldglover.jpg.webp 1x" media="all and (max-width: 314px)" type="image/webp" width="450" height="253">
                  

  </picture>


  
  
  
</article>

<p>Yoshi will be voiced by Donald Glover, AKA Childish Gambino, the actor/rapper best known for his roles in <em>Community</em>, <em>Solo: A Star Wars Story</em>, <em>Spider-Man: Homecoming</em>, and <em>The Lion King</em>.</p>



<article data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="0bb9547d-9731-4433-bb95-c5917b1ddb65" data-embed-button="image_browser_uploader" data-entity-embed-display="image:responsive_image" data-entity-embed-display-settings="{&quot;responsive_image_style&quot;:&quot;content_body&quot;,&quot;image_loading&quot;:{&quot;attribute&quot;:&quot;lazy&quot;},&quot;image_link&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;link_url&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;link_target&quot;:0,&quot;link_original&quot;:0,&quot;image_source&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;embed_source&quot;:0,&quot;image_caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;embed_caption&quot;:0,&quot;content_warning&quot;:0}" data-langcode="en">

  
          <picture>
                  <source srcset="https://gameinformer.com/sites/default/files/styles/body_default/public/2026/03/09/07bb95fc/supermariogalaxymovie_luisguzman.jpg.webp 1x" media="all and (min-width: 851px)" type="image/webp" width="800" height="450">
              <source srcset="https://gameinformer.com/sites/default/files/styles/content_default_mobile_/public/2026/03/09/07bb95fc/supermariogalaxymovie_luisguzman.jpg.webp 1x" media="all and (min-width: 315px) and (max-width: 450px)" type="image/webp" width="450" height="253">
              <source srcset="https://gameinformer.com/sites/default/files/styles/content_default_mobile_/public/2026/03/09/07bb95fc/supermariogalaxymovie_luisguzman.jpg.webp 1x" media="all and (max-width: 314px)" type="image/webp" width="450" height="253">
                  

  </picture>


  
  
  
</article>

<p>Luis Guzmán will portray Wart, the evil frog king best known as the big bad in Super Mario Bros. 2 (U.S. version). Guzmán’s long list of credits includes TV series like <em>Oz</em> and <em>Wednesday</em> and films such as<em> Carlito’s Way</em>, <em>Boogie Nights</em>, <em>Punch-Drunk Love</em>, and Traffic.</p>



<article data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="c76a4618-37ae-4626-9dd1-60c561719c6d" data-embed-button="image_browser_uploader" data-entity-embed-display="image:responsive_image" data-entity-embed-display-settings="{&quot;responsive_image_style&quot;:&quot;content_body&quot;,&quot;image_loading&quot;:{&quot;attribute&quot;:&quot;lazy&quot;},&quot;image_link&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;link_url&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;link_target&quot;:0,&quot;link_original&quot;:0,&quot;image_source&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;embed_source&quot;:0,&quot;image_caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;embed_caption&quot;:0,&quot;content_warning&quot;:0}" data-langcode="en">

  
          <picture>
                  <source srcset="https://gameinformer.com/sites/default/files/styles/body_default/public/2026/03/09/09c31dec/supermariogalaxymovie_issarae.jpg.webp 1x" media="all and (min-width: 851px)" type="image/webp" width="800" height="450">
              <source srcset="https://gameinformer.com/sites/default/files/styles/content_default_mobile_/public/2026/03/09/09c31dec/supermariogalaxymovie_issarae.jpg.webp 1x" media="all and (min-width: 315px) and (max-width: 450px)" type="image/webp" width="450" height="253">
              <source srcset="https://gameinformer.com/sites/default/files/styles/content_default_mobile_/public/2026/03/09/09c31dec/supermariogalaxymovie_issarae.jpg.webp 1x" media="all and (max-width: 314px)" type="image/webp" width="450" height="253">
                  

  </picture>


  
  
  
</article>

<p>Lastly, Honey Queen, ruler of the Honey Hive galaxy, will be played by Issa Rae. Rae is perhaps best known as the star of HBO’s <em>Insecure</em>, but she has also appeared in films such as <em>Little</em>, <em>Barbie</em>, and <em>American Fiction</em>.</p><p><em>The Super Mario Galaxy Movie</em> hits theaters on April 1. You can watch the first trailer <a href="https://gameinformer.com/nintendo-direct/2025/11/12/the-super-mario-galaxy-movie-casts-brie-larson-as-rosalina-benny-safdie">here</a> and the second trailer <a href="https://gameinformer.com/2026/01/26/yoshi-debuts-in-second-super-mario-galaxy-movie-trailer">here</a>.&nbsp;</p></div></div><br/><br/>https://gameinformer.com/2026/03/09/nintendo-reveals-the-final-trailer-for-the-super-mario-galaxy-movie-and-voice-cast-for]]></content:encoded>
